I find myself on the beach with a pounding headache and no memories except for being tortured in a dark room. Survival is my top priority now, but I have nothing. I'll scour the surroundings for materials to make a shelter and tools. A bed to sleep on and something to satisfy my hunger would be great too.

The Marauders are a notorious band of pirates who specifically target weaker and more vulnerable settlements and vessels. Although they may lack advanced equipment compared to other pirate groups, their sheer numbers and ruthless tactics compensate for this. It is undeniable that eliminating them would greatly benefit the people of Sunkenland.

The Skull Crushers, a brutal bandit clan, has seized the sunken downtown area, perching atop submerged skyscrapers. Their threat looms large as they hoard vital resources and launch relentless attacks. It's time to confront and defeat these marauders, ensuring a prosperous future. But beware, they're armed and dangerous.

Infiltrate and neutralize the Scorchers, a deadly bandit faction occupying the abandoned nuclear power plant. Armed to the teeth and backed by a mutant army, they pose a grave threat. Prepare for radiation exposure, wear protective gear, and carry anti-rad meds. Take down the Scorchers, claim valuable loot, and restore peace to the region.

If you last played in v0.1.04 and want to retain your progress, switch to the Olderversion branch now. If you played after the v0.1.10 update (released on Thursday), you're good to go.\x0A\x0A\x0ATo switch to v0.1.04: In the Steam Library, right-click the game, select 'Properties', go to the 'BETAS' tab, and choose 'olderversion0104' from the drop-down menu.\x0AAfter switching, load the game as usual, and place all your inventory items, including the hotbar and equipment, into a storage chest in your base. Then save the game and switch back to the main branch. Please note that blueprints will be affected in any case.\x0A(To switch back, repeat the process and select 'None - opt out of all beta programs'.)\x0A\x0A\x0ALoading saves in this version will erase your inventory and blueprints, but your buildings should remain intact.\x0A\x0A\x0AWe've overhauled the game's core coding to address saving/loading issues, resulting in faster saving and more stable loading. We've also improved world stability (tested with 30k building pieces). Unfortunately, these changes led to save conflicts.
